CLI Reference

The Lakehouse Plumber command-line interface provides project creation, validation, code generation, state inspection and more. All commands are implemented with click so you can use the usual --help flags.

lhp

LakehousePlumber - Generate Delta Live Tables pipelines from YAML configs.

lhp [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...

Options

--version

Show the version and exit.

-v, --verbose

Enable verbose logging

generate

Generate DLT pipeline code

lhp generate [OPTIONS]

Options

-e, --env <env>

Required Environment

-p, --pipeline <pipeline>

Specific pipeline to generate

-o, --output <output>

Output directory

--dry-run

Preview without generating files

--format

Format generated code with Black

--cleanup

Clean up generated files when source YAML files are removed (similar to Terraform state management)

-f, --force

Force regeneration of all files, even if unchanged

info

Display project information and statistics.

lhp info [OPTIONS]

init

Initialize a new LakehousePlumber project

lhp init [OPTIONS] PROJECT_NAME

Arguments

PROJECT_NAME

Required argument

list-presets

List available presets

lhp list-presets [OPTIONS]

list-templates

List available templates

lhp list-templates [OPTIONS]

setup-intellisense

Set up VS Code IntelliSense support for Lakehouse Plumber YAML files.

lhp setup-intellisense [OPTIONS]

Options

--status

Show current IntelliSense setup status

--check

Check prerequisites for IntelliSense setup

--verify

Verify that IntelliSense setup is working correctly

--cleanup

Remove IntelliSense setup and schema associations

--force

Force setup even if prerequisites are not met

--conflicts

Show extension conflict analysis

show

Show resolved configuration for a flowgroup in table format

lhp show [OPTIONS] FLOWGROUP

Options

-e, --env <env>

Environment

Arguments

FLOWGROUP

Required argument

state

Show or manage the current state of generated files.

lhp state [OPTIONS]

Options

-e, --env <env>

Environment to show state for

-p, --pipeline <pipeline>

Specific pipeline to show state for

--orphaned

Show only orphaned files

--stale

Show only stale files (YAML changed)

--new

Show only new/untracked YAML files

--dry-run

Preview cleanup without actually deleting files

--cleanup

Clean up orphaned files

--regen

Regenerate stale files

stats

Display pipeline statistics and complexity metrics.

lhp stats [OPTIONS]

Options

-p, --pipeline <pipeline>

Specific pipeline to analyze

validate

Validate pipeline configurations

lhp validate [OPTIONS]

Options

-e, --env <env>

Environment

-p, --pipeline <pipeline>

Specific pipeline to validate

-v, --verbose

Verbose output
